10 SECTION 9. IC 10-18-1-30 IS REPEALED [EFFECTIVE UPON
11 PASSAGE]. Sec. 30. (a) The commission may not enter into a contract
12 for:
13 (1) the purchase or sale of property, material, or supplies; or
14 (2) the performance of work or labor, except for salaries of
15 employees;
16 if the work and labor or materials and supplies cost more than ten
17 thousand dollars ($10,000) without first giving notice of its intention
18 to purchase or sell the materials or supplies or to contract for the work
19 or labor by publication in a newspaper of general circulation printed
20 and published in the English language in Indianapolis for two (2)
21 successive weeks before the time fixed for the letting of the contract or
22 the sale of the property.
23 (b) A contract under this section must be in writing. The other
24 contracting party shall furnish bond for the faithful performance of the
25 contract in an amount fixed by the commission and with surety to the
26 commission's approval, conditioned upon the faithful performance of
27 the contract. However, if the commission decides to purchase a
28 patented article or material or an article or material of a special type,
29 character, or design of construction or make that may be purchased
30 from only one (1) person, firm, limited liability company, or
31 corporation, their agents or representatives, or for which there is a
32 fixed, standard price, the commission is not required to take or receive
33 competitive bids. However, the commission shall publish in the manner
34 set forth under subsection (a) the number and character of the article
35 or kind and quality of material proposed to be purchased, the unit price,
36 and the total sum to be paid.
37 (c) A contract made in violation of this section is void.
